i.TH LIVS-DWM 1 "August 2025" "Liv's dwm build" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
livs-dwm \- a dynamic, but surprisingly feature-rich, window manager for X
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B livs-dwm
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B livs-dwm
is Liv's personal, heavily patched build of
.BR dwm .
It manages windows in tiled, monocle, and floating layouts. All of the layouts can be applied dynamically, optimizing the environment for the application in use and the task performed. It is keyboard-driven, ridiculously fast, and famously configured by editing a C header file and recompiling.
.PP
You have taken the minimalist philosophy of
.B dwm
and said, "Yes, but what if it did... more?" This build is the glorious result. It has gaps, it has transparency, it has keychords, it even has a systray! It swallows windows, starts its own apps, and can be restarted without making all your windows flee in terror.
.PP
If it breaks, you get to keep both pieces and the unique learning experience of debugging your own window manager. You wanted control, you got it.
.SH PATCHES APPLIED
This build isn't your grandfather's
.BR dwm .
It has been augmented with the following digital appendages:
.TP
.B dwm-alpha-systray
For making your terminal just transparent enough to see the anime wallpaper behind it, and for wrangling tray icons.
.TP
.B dwm-autostart
Executes
.I ~/.dwm/autostart.sh
on startup. Because typing the same commands every time is for the birds.
.TP
.B dwm-cfacts-vanitygaps
Gives you pixel-perfect control over window gaps and sizing factors. For the true digital feng shui master.
.TP
.B dwm-customrefreshrate
So your window dragging is as buttery-smooth as your 165Hz monitor.
.TP
.B dwm-cyclelayouts & dwm-cyclewindows
Lets you spin through your open layouts and windows like a game show wheel.
.TP
.B dwm-default-tag-apps
Because your browser should
.I always
open on tag 2. It's just natural.
.TP
.B dwm-desktop_icons
Wait, icons? On the desktop? In
.I my
.BR dwm?
A concession to modernity we shall not speak of again.
.TP
.B dwm-fadeinactive
Makes unfocused windows politely fade into the background, highlighting your current masterpiece of procrastination.
.TP
.B dwm-fullscreen-compilation-noborder
Because when a window is fullscreen, it should be
.I actually
fullscreen. No questions asked.
.TP
.B dwm-games
What does it do? We're not sure. Probably adds +5 FPS to your
.I nethack
sessions.
.TP
.B dwm-hide_vacant_tags
Keeps your bar tidy by hiding tags that have no windows. Minimalism strikes back.
.TP
.B dwm-keychord
The heart of this build's efficiency. Turns your keyboard into a multi-layered command center.
.TP
.B dwm-make_ewmh_windows_float
Tells misbehaving dialog boxes from GIMP and friends to open as floating windows, as nature intended.
.TP
.B dwm-restartsig
Lets you restart
.B dwm
in-place with a keypress. Recompile and reload without losing your precious layout.
.TP
.B dwm-spotifyworkaround
Sometimes, you have to fight for your right to party. This patch makes Spotify behave.
.TP
.B dwm-swallow
Enables a terminal to "swallow" a GUI window it launches, automatically replacing it when the GUI program exits. Efficient and oddly satisfying.
